The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | School stick for 2 kids
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      School stick for 2 kids
                            
	Barasat, Sept. 25: Two Class II students have landed in hospital after being allegedly beaten up by a teacher for failing a class test yesterday.         
	Fuli Khatun and Motiar Mondal of Gopinathpur Primary School in Gopalnagar near Bongaon were among eight students allegedly beaten up by the geography teacher for failing the test.         
	Fuli and Motiar suffered head and back injuries. Motiar has been discharged after treatment. Fulis father has lodged an FIR against the teacher. The teacher said he had to beat the students to make them learn from their mistakes.                                                                                                                                                            
